# {{workspace_label}}

This repository is the DRAFT architecture workspace for {{company_name}}. It
vendors the DRAFT framework under `.draft/framework/`; that vendored copy is
the approved source for schemas, RequirementGroups, base configurations,
templates, docs, and tools.

## AI Bootstrap

- Canonical AI instructions: AGENTS.md
- Draftsman role: .draft/framework/docs/draftsman.md
- Draftsman setup mode: .draft/framework/docs/setup-mode.md
- Framework index: .draft/framework/AI_INDEX.md
- Workspace metadata: .draft/workspace.yaml
- {{company_name}} vocabulary: .draft/workspace.yaml and configurations/vocabulary/
- Schema reference: .draft/framework/docs/yaml-schema-reference.md
- Validation command: python .draft/framework/tools/validate.py --workspace .

## Write Boundary

- {{company_name}} architecture content: catalog/
- {{company_name}} configuration overlays and vocabulary proposals: configurations/
- Generated browser: docs/index.html
- Framework-managed, read-only during normal Draftsman work: .draft/framework/**
- Framework sync state, read-only during normal Draftsman work: .draft/framework.lock

If drafting reveals a likely reusable DRAFT framework bug or feature request,
recommend a sanitized upstream issue in public `getdraft/draftsman`; ask before
creating it and use the framework bug or feature template.

If an AI assistant is connected only to the upstream `draft-framework` repo and
the user asks for {{company_name}} content changes, ask for the company-specific DRAFT
repo path before editing.
